# Movie Finder — Project Context

Full-stack AI app: user describes a half-remembered film → semantic search (Qdrant) → IMDb enrichment → streamed Q&A chat via SSE.

## Submodule map

| Open this workspace      | Repo                            | Role                                     |
|--------------------------|---------------------------------|------------------------------------------|
| root (`movie-finder/`)   | `aharbii/movie-finder`          | Orchestrator — all cross-repo issues     |
| `backend/`               | `aharbii/movie-finder-backend`  | FastAPI + uv workspace root              |
| `backend/chain/`         | `aharbii/movie-finder-chain`    | LangGraph 8-node AI pipeline             |
| `frontend/`              | `aharbii/movie-finder-frontend` | Angular 21 SPA                           |
| `docs/`                  | `aharbii/movie-finder-docs`     | MkDocs + PlantUML + Structurizr + ADRs   |
| `infrastructure/`        | `aharbii/movie-finder-infrastructure` | Azure IaC                          |

## Stack at a glance

- **Backend:** Python 3.13, FastAPI 0.115+, asyncpg, LangGraph 0.2+, LangChain 0.3+
- **AI models:** Claude Haiku (classify), Claude Sonnet (reason/Q&A)
- **Embeddings:** OpenAI `text-embedding-3-large` (3072-dim)
- **Vector store:** Qdrant Cloud — always external, no local container ever
- **Frontend:** Angular 21, TypeScript 5.9, Signals, SSE (`EventSource`)
- **DB:** PostgreSQL 16 via asyncpg — no Alembic yet (issue #3)
- **CI/CD:** Jenkins → Azure Container Registry → Azure Container Apps

## Key commands

```bash
make up              # start full stack in Docker
make down            # stop all containers
make mkdocs          # docs site → http://localhost:8001
make structurizr     # C4 diagrams → http://localhost:18080
gh issue list --repo aharbii/movie-finder --state open   # check open work
```

## Non-negotiables

- Never `git add -A` — submodule gitlinks and secrets can be staged accidentally
- Never `--no-verify` on pre-commit hooks
- Never push directly to `main` — PRs required, 1 approval
- Never commit secrets — `detect-secrets` pre-commit hook enforces this
- Never instantiate shared resources inside route handlers — use FastAPI `Depends()`
- Conventional Commits: `type(scope): summary` — types: feat · fix · chore · docs · test · refactor · perf
- Disclose AI tool + model in every PR description and review comment

## Branching

```
main  ← always deployable, protected
  └── feature/<kebab-case>
  └── fix/<kebab-case>
  └── chore/<kebab-case>   ← submodule pointer bumps go here
  └── docs/<kebab-case>
  └── hotfix/<kebab-case>
```

